<concept id="concept_E8D43EB4494E41D2AB42D4A89396D1AB"
                    xml:lang="en-us">
    <title>Readers of this Manual</title>
    <conbody>
        <section>
            <p>This manual is written for operators who install, operate, and maintain <ph
                    conref="../../shared/product-name.xml#ProductNameTopic/Product_Abbr"
                    />. It also describes how the operator uses <ph
                    conref="../../shared/product-name.xml#ProductNameTopic/Product_Abbr"/> for monitoring. </p>
            <p>The manual assumes that you have profound knowledge of OpenStack and <ph
                    conref="../../shared/product-name.xml#ProductNameTopic/Product_Abbr"
                    />, especially the individual services <ph
                    conref="../../shared/product-name.xml#ProductNameTopic/Product_Abbr"
                    /> is composed of. For installing the <ph
                    conref="../../shared/product-name.xml#ProductNameTopic/Product_Abbr"
                /> components, you must be familiar with the administration and operation of LINUX systems.</p>
        </section>
    </conbody>
</concept>
